Project: Personal Portfolio Website

Description: Create a personal portfolio website showcasing your skills, projects, and experiences. This project will involve building the front-end of the website using HTML, CSS, and possibly JavaScript.

Features:

Home: A landing page introducing yourself with a brief bio and a profile picture.
Portfolio: Showcase your projects with descriptions, screenshots, and links.
About Me: Share more details about your background, skills, and interests.
Contact: Provide a way for visitors to get in touch with you, like a contact form or social media links.
Technologies:

HTML: Structure the content of the web pages.
CSS: Style the layout, fonts, colors, and responsiveness of the website.
Optional: JavaScript for interactive elements like animations or filtering projects.
Steps:

Plan the website structure and layout.
Create the HTML files for each page.
Style the website using CSS to make it visually appealing.
Add interactivity using JavaScript if desired.
Test the website on different devices and browsers.
Deploy the website to a hosting platform like GitHub Pages or Netlify.
